<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="438" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1852,2023]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">
I agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Gowlett-Holmes, K." box="[289,556,1852,1879]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" pagination="19 - 84" refId="ref17314" refString="Gowlett-Holmes, K. (2001) Polyplacophora. In: Wells, A. &amp; Houston, W. W. K. (Eds.), Zoological Catalog of Australia. Vol. 17.2. Mollusca: Aplacophora, Polyplacophora, Scaphopoda, Cephalopoda. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, pp. 19 - 84." type="book chapter" year="2001">Gowlett-Holmes (2001)</bibRefCitation>
who did not find insertion plates in the 
<typeStatus box="[995,1043,1853,1879]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
and other materials and transferred this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1847" box="[424,558,1888,1914]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[424,558,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Iredale &amp; Hull (1924), who included this species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale &amp; Hull, 1924" authorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" authorityYear="1924" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Subterenochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1254,1437,1888,1914]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Subterenochiton</emphasis>
Iredale &amp; Hull, 1924
</taxonomicName>
mentioned posterior gills in the 
<typeStatus box="[745,793,1925,1951]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
specimen, which is typical for leptochitonids. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hull, 1912)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1912" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Subterenochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gabrieli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Subterenochiton gabrieli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hull, A. F. B." box="[337,465,1960,1987]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" pagination="120 - 121" refId="ref17803" refString="Hull, A. F. B. (1912) Description of two new Ischnochitons from Western Port, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, New Series, New Series, 25 (1), 120 - 121." type="journal article" year="1912">Hull, 1912</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[531,579,1961,1987]" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" authorityYear="1924" box="[830,1012,1960,1986]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Ischnochitonidae" genus="Subterenochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chitonida" pageId="37" pageNumber="438" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[830,1012,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="438">Subterenochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, has13 gills arranged from valve II to valve VII which is typical of more derived species.
</paragraph>
